0fighter%20developed%20jointly%20by%20China%20and%20Turkey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e88c73ce7f1785b2e6c781%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAzerbaijan%20is%20reportedly%20striking%20a%20deal%20for%20the%20JF-17%20Thunder%20fighter%20developed%20jointly%20by%20China%20and%20Turkey.%3Cp%3EMiguel%20Medina%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAzerbaijan's%20biggest%20arms%20supplier%20has%20been%20Russia%20but%20it%20will%20likely%20acquire%20jets%20from%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20rumored%20deal%20suggests%20the%20longtime%20ally%20is%20detaching%20more%20from%20Moscow%2C%20a%20defense%20analyst%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20answer%20to%20America's%20F-22%20and%20F-35%2C%20the%20Su-57%2C%20has%20severe%20shortcomings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20small%2C%20oil-rich%20South%20Caucasus%20country%20of%20Azerbaijan%20has%20big%20plans%20to%20upgrade%20its%20modest%20fleet%20of%20fighter%20jets%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%20However%2C%20rather%20than%20turn%20to%20Russia%2C%20its%20traditional%20arms%20supplier%20for%20decades%2C%20Baku%20will%20likely%20acquire%20modern%20fighters%20from%20Pakistan%20and%20Turkey.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20turn%20away%20from%20Russia%20shows%20that%20longtime%20allies%20like%20Azerbaijan%20are%20finding%20effective%20arms%20sellers%20who%20aren't%20afflicted%20by%20the%20problems%20of%20Russia's%20newest%20fighter%20jets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnconfirmed%20reports%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.azernews.az%2Fnation%2F222206.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAzerbaijani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpakobserver.net%2Fpakistan-seals-1-6-billion-deal-with-azerbaijan-to-sell-jf-17-fighter-jets%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPakistani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20media%20surfaced%20in%20late%20February%20claiming%20Azerbaijan%20reached%20a%20deal%20with%20Pakistan%20to%20buy%20an%20undisclosed%20number%20of%20JF-17C%20Thunder%20fighter%20jets%20for%20%241.6%20billion.%20Azerbaijan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2024%2F02%2Fturkish-5th-gen-fighter-kaan-completes-maiden-flight%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eofficially%20joined%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Turkey's%20TF%20Kaan%20fifth-generation%20fighter%20program%20last%20July%2C%20strongly%20suggesting%20it%20will%20acquire%20that%20jet.%20The%20Kaan%20made%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popularmechanics.com%2Fmilitary%2Faviation%2Fa46961799%2Fturkeys-very-first-fighter-jet-made-its-history-shattering-flight%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emaiden%20flight%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20February.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia%20previously%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defenseone.com%2Fbusiness%2F2024%2F02%2Fwill-azerbaijan-buy-pakistani-fighter-jets%2F394504%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emarketed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%204.5-generation%20Su-30SM%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.azernews.az%2Fnation%2F163963.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESu-35%2C%20and%20MiG-35%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fighters%20to%20Azerbaijan%20in%20the%20late%202010s.%20Azerbaijan's%20president%20said%20in%202018%20that%20his%20country%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sipri.org%2Fcommentary%2Ftopical-backgrounder%2F2021%2Farms-transfers-conflict-zones-case-nagorno-karabakh%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Espent%20%245%20billion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Russian%20military%20hardware.%20But%20now%20it%20doesn't%20seem%20likely%20Baku%20will%20turn%20to%20Moscow%20for%204.5-generation%20aircraft.%20Azerbaijan%20is%20even%20less%20likely%20to%20invest%20in%20Russia's%20troubled%205th-generation%20Su-57%20or%20Su-75%20%26quot%3BCheckmate%26quot%3B%20jets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia%20has%20been%20Azerbaijan's%20largest%20arms%20supplier%20until%20recent%20years%2C%20said%20Frederico%20Borsari%2C%20a%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20European%20Policy%20Analysis%20(CEPA).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20things%20have%20progressively%20changed%20as%20Russia%20launched%20a%20reckless%20war%20of%20aggression%20against%20Ukraine%20and%20started%20to%20lose%20influence%20among%20countries%20in%20the%20Caucasus%20amidst%20growing%20difficulties%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20financial%20constraints%2C%26quot%3B%20Borsari%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BTurkey%2C%20among%20others%2C%20has%20exploited%20this%20situation%20from%20a%20security%20standpoint%20and%20started%20to%20expand%20its%20military%20cooperation%20with%20Baku%2C%20including%20through%20weapons%20sales.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConsequently%2C%20Turkish%20sales%20to%20Azerbaijan%20began%20increasing%20in%202017%2C%20while%20Russian%20arms%20exports%20halted%20around%202019.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BAgainst%20this%20backdrop%2C%20the%20rumored%20JF-17%20purchase%20from%20Pakistan%20further%20consolidates%20this%20trend%20of%20progressive%20detachment%20from%20Moscow's%20fold%20and%20may%20also%20be%20the%20result%20of%20the%20poor%20performance%20of%20Russian%20aircraft%20(and%20the%20air%20force%20overall)%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20Borsari%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESebastien%20Roblin%2C%20a%20widely%20published%20military-aviation%20journalist%2C%20says%20it%20is%20understandable%20if%20Azerbaijan%20decides%20to%20use%20its%20oil%20wealth%20to%20overhaul%20its%20manned%20fighter%20fleet%20until%20the%20Kaan%20begins%20rolling%20off%20production%20lines%20%26quot%3Bin%20quantity%26quot%3B%20around%202033.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20close%20relations%20with%20Turkey%20and%20ambivalent%20ones%20with%20Russia%2C%20its%20preference%20for%20the%20latter%20is%20understandable%2C%20particularly%20given%20Russia's%20own%20problems%20bringing%20Su-57s%20into%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20Roblin%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERoblin%20noted%20that%20Azerbaijan%20faces%20%26quot%3Btricky%20considerations%26quot%3B%20when%20weighing%20a%20%26quot%3Bpolitically%20reliable%20vendor%26quot%3B%20for%20new%20fighters.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BNeither%20Russia%20nor%20Western%20democracies%20are%20ideal%20suppliers%2C%20even%20though%20Russia%20has%20historically%20sold%20arms%20to%20Azerbaijan%2C%26quot%3B%20Roblin%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BPakistan%20and%20Turkey%2C%20and%20through%20Pakistan%2C%20China%2C%20may%20seem%20like%20more%20reliable%20partners%20for%20Baku%20unlikely%20to%20cut%20off%20deals%20due%20to%20upset%20over%20human%20rights%20issues%20or%20future%20potential%20wars%20with%20Armenia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBorsari%20said%20Azerbaijan's%20participation%20in%20the%20Kaan%20project%20is%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20and%20foremost%20the%20natural%20consequence%20of%20a%20long-standing%20and%20growing%20security%20partnership%26quot%3B%20between%20Ankara%20and%20Baku%20that%20stems%20from%20their%20close%20political%20and%20diplomatic%20ties.%20Turkey%20provided%20training%20and%20arms%20that%20enabled%20Azerbaijan%20to%20defeat%20Armenia's%20armed%20forces%20in%20the%202020%20war%20over%20the%20Nagorno-Karabakh%20enclave.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BFor%20both%20countries%2C%20this%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20win-win%20solution%2C%26quot%3B%20Borsari%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20choice%20would%20allow%20long-term%20and%20robust%20cooperation%20that%20ensures%20the%20sustainability%20of%20Baku's%20air%20force%20in%20terms%20of%20logistics%2C%20training%2C%20maintenance%2C%20etc%2C%20with%20a%20close%20ally%20while%20providing%20Turkey%20with%20a%20long-term%20contract%20and%20client%20in%20the%20defense%20sector.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CEPA%20analyst%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bprospective%20problems%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20Russian%20military%20aircraft%20industry%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20disappointment%20surrounding%20the%20Su-57%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bpoor%20performance%26quot%3B%20of%20other%20Russian%20fighters%20in%20Ukraine%20are%20other%20possible%20factors%20that%20pushed%20Baku%20%26quot%3Bto%20opt%20for%20Turkey's%20project.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20Russia%20has%20promoted%20the%20Su-57%20as%20its%20answer%20to%20America's%20F-22%20and%20F-35%2C%20the%20fifth-generation%20fighter%20has%20exhibited%20some%20severe%20shortcomings.%20Analysts%20have%20noted%20it%20lacks%20fifth-generation%20engines%2C%20and%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffifth-generation-jets-made-ukraine-war-russia-su-57-missing-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebody%20panels%20are%20not%20placed%20tightly%20enough%20together%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20reduce%20the%20aircraft's%20radar%20cross-section%20%E2%80%94%20a%20key%20feature%20in%20any%20stealth%20aircraft.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20Azerbaijani%20acquisition%20of%20the%20JF-17%2C%20which%20the%20Pakistan%20Aeronautical%20Complex%20and%20China's%20Chengdu%20Aircraft%20Corporation%20jointly%20developed%2C%20would%20also%20be%20significant.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225688%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Sukhoi%20Su-57%20jet%20fighter%20performs%20during%20the%20MAKS%202021%20air%20show%20in%20Zhukovsky%2C%20outside%20Moscow%2C%20Russia%2C%20July%2025%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%