024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20couple's%20Massachusetts%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Grace%20Lucchese%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMickey%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOur%20home%20was%20originally%20listed%20for%20%24429%2C000.%20When%20we%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-how-to-negotiate-best-price-down-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegotiating%20with%20the%20seller%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20trying%20to%20talk%20him%20down%20on%20the%20price%2C%20they%20brought%20up%20the%20assumable%20loan%20%E2%80%94%20I%20had%20no%20clue%20what%20that%20type%20of%20mortgage%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrace%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20An%20assumable%20mortgage%20is%20not%20a%20new%20loan%2C%20you're%20just%20taking%20over%20the%20owner's%20loan%20term%20and%20interest%20rate.%20At%20first%2C%20it%20sounded%20too%20good%20to%20be%20true.%20When%20we%20were%20first%20looking%20for%20homes%2C%20the%20interest%20rate%20was%20around%20the%20higher%20sevens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrace%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20talked%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-lowest-best-mortgage-rate-payment-assumable-mortgage-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassumable%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20about%20a%20day%20and%20decided%20we%20were%20going%20to%20go%20for%20it.%20We%20put%20an%20offer%20on%20the%20house%20on%20September%2027%20and%20finally%20closed%20on%20January%2016.%20We%20made%20a%20down%20payment%20of%20%2413%2C000%20and%20purchased%20our%20home%20for%20%24422%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%202.6%25%20interest%20rate.%20If%20we%20took%20out%20a%20regular%20veteran%20(VA)%20home%20loan%2C%20our%20payment%20was%20going%20to%20be%20around%20%244%2C200%20each%20month.%20But%20with%20the%20assumable%20loan%2C%20our%20monthly%20payment%20went%20down%20to%20%241%2C700.%20With%20homeowners'%20insurance%20included%2C%20it's%20about%20%2